snippet.textDisplay: People love to compare LeBron to Kawhi and I understand why. They're both 2 great players. Because of all that LeBron has done ,we expect a lot from him, but the reality of the situation is Lebron is has played 16 seasons in the NBA to Kawhi's... 8 I think. LeBron has certainly been in way more playoff games. Kawhi is 28. LeBron is 34. Age is a factor here. So is wear and tear on the body. I'm not making excuses for LeBron, but it just is what it is. The fact this his lackluster performances are still better than more than half the league at this point in his career is still pretty amazing.
